text_en:
What you are going to do
Are you passionate about the field of HRM? Would you like to showcase your proactive attitude? Can you also work in an organized manner? Then we are looking for you! You will closely work with the HR manager of the company. You will work in the HR department in an all-round position. The role is a challenging job, in which you will deal with various aspects of HR. Before the HR manager approaches you, you already have everything arranged. You are quick and capable of keeping the administrative tasks in order. You are someone who gets energy from setting up processes and you are good with computers. There is plenty of room for personal input in the role and you are given the freedom to further develop yourself. Some of the tasks include: processing sick leave notifications, organizing and setting up the recruitment, selection, and onboarding process; being the point of contact for new candidates; creating employment contracts; keeping the personnel files up to date.

About the company
You will be working for an ambitious and innovative organization. They mainly focus on offering software to automate business processes. This allows administrative processes to be completed faster and more easily. This saves a lot of time for customers, such as businesses and accountants. The company is located in a beautiful old building in the heart of The Hague and is easily accessible by private transport and public transportation.

Job requirements
You enjoy helping the most important people in the organization, the employees, move forward! Furthermore, you can describe yourself at work as independent, organizationally aware, and customer-oriented. Additionally, you recognize yourself in the following:
- You have completed a vocational or HBO (higher professional education) HRM program;
- You have strong communication and writing skills;
- You are eager to learn and would like to expand your experience in HR;
- You have problem-solving skills.

What we offer you
In addition to working in an enthusiastic organization with a friendly team, they offer the following:
- A gross salary between €2,500 and €3,200 per month based on 40 hours;
- A permanent position for 32-40 hours per week full-time;
- A fixed-term contract with the possibility of extension;
- Possibility of hybrid working;
- Well-catered lunch.
